Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Once boiled, pour the water into a #saucepan{},
add @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta. Add the @penne pasta{200%g} and simmer until
cooked, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the
pan and add a little @olive oil{} to stop the pasta sticking together.

Whilst the pasta cooks, trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed), then quarter lengthways.
Chop widthways into small pieces. Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large
#frying pan{} over a medium high heat. When hot, add the chopped courgette and
fry, stirring frequently until it begins to soften, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Whilst the courgette cooks, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled
and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and
grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Add the garlic and cook for a further
~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the courgette and garlic from the pan and transfer to a
#plate{} for later.

Add another splash of @oil{another splash} to the pan and pop back on a medium
high heat. When hot, add the chopped onion and fry, stirring frequently until
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @tomato puree{30%g} and water (see
ingredients for amount), and stir to combine. Bring to the boil then reduce the
heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Crumble three quarters
of the @feta cheese{100%g} into the sauce, stir until it has melted in. Simmer
gently, stirring until the sauce is smooth and has reduced slightly,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the feta has melted and the sauce is smooth, add the @king prawns{150%g}.
Cook the prawns in the sauce stirring gently, ~{3-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The
prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle. Then add
the cooked courgette and garlic and stir through.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and combine, taste and add @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the liquid has evaporated too much.

Divide between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle the remaining feta on-top of each
portion. Enjoy!